Question 2.

What is the distribution of backpack weights that students are carrying? Choose an appropriate graph to show the distribution.

backpack %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = backpack_weight) +
  geom_bar()


backpack %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = backpack_weight) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, colour="black", fill="white") +
    geom_vline(aes(xintercept=mean(backpack_weight, na.rm=TRUE)),   # Ignore NA values for mean
               color="red", linetype="dashed", size=1)

Question 6.

What proportion of students report back pain?

# backpack %>% 
#   group_by(back_problems) %>% 
#   summarise(count = n()) %>% 
  ggplot(backpack) +
  aes(x = back_problems) +
  geom_bar() +
    labs(
      x = "back problems",
      y = "count",
      title = "Proportion with and without back problems") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0,1), labels = c("no", "yes")) +
  #scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0,1), labels = c("No", "Yes"))
  theme_minimal()

Question 7.

Is this proportion different between men and women?

2 ways to label the x axis


ggplot(backpack) +
  aes(x = back_problems) + 
  geom_bar() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(0,1), labels = c("No", "Yes"))


backpack %>%
  mutate(back_problems = as.logical(back_problems)) %>%
ggplot() +
  aes(x = back_problems) + 
  geom_bar() +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("No", "Yes"))
